<TEXT>
separate drug busts in methuen mass and san diego and lake 
city calif netted 1900 pounds of cocaine and chemicals to make 
some 2500 pounds of methamphetamine authorities said friday 
in massachusetts federal agents friday seized 1200 pounds of 
cocaine 
four colombian nationals were arrested following the noon raid 
which culminated a twoyear investigation into international drug 
trafficking said drug enforcement agency special agent john coleman 
us customs officials seized the cocaine at a public storage 
facility in methuen the shipment had been destined for the new york 
city area said leonard walton special agent in charge of the 
customs services boston office he said more arrests were expected 
but declined to give details 
in california more than 700 pounds of cocaine stashed in two 
pickup trucks were seized when authorities intercepted the alleged 
smugglers during a thursday night crossing into the united states 
from mexico officials said friday 
agents of the san diego county integrated narcotics task force 
acting on information gathered during a threemonth undercover 
investigation staked out the san ysidro port of entry and waited 
for the vehicles to cross said san diego police lt skip dicerchio 
eight boxes stuffed with hundreds of 1pound packages of cocaine 
were found in the trucks dicerchio said along with 23000 in cash 
the men were booked for investigation of conspiracy to import 
cocaine and conspiracy to import a controlled substance 
elsewhere in california authorities said they plan to issue 
arrest warrants next week for five people in the discovery of a lab 
where drug agents found enough chemicals to make some 2500 pounds 
of methamphetamine or speed 
modoc county sheriff bruce mix said the lab and chemicals were 
discovered earlier this week in a raid near lake city about 300 
miles northeast of sacramento near the californianevada line 
