in favor a coors spokesman said 
the balloting followed 18 months of union and company politicking 
at the brewery the nations fourth largest coors has 1600 brewery 
workers 
it came out loud and clear that theyre satisfied at this 
time dave laughton a teamsters leader 
we are delighted that our employees have decided that 
thirdparty representation is not needed at coors said peter 
