the jury of eight women and four men debated the complex case for 
4 hours thursday and recessed until this morning chief us 
district judge albert v bryan jr said they should be prepared to 
work through saturday if necessary to decide all 49 counts involved 
larouche and six associates were charged with mail fraud and 
conspiracy for allegedly raising more than 30 million in loans from 
supporters without any intention of repaying them 
in addition larouche 66 was charged with conspiring to defraud 
the internal revenue service by having all his personal expenses 
paid by various corporations he controls and claiming he had no 
taxable income 
larouche has not filed federal income tax returns for any year 
since 1978 government prosecutors say 
if convicted of all 13 counts against him larouche faces a 
maximum penalty of 65 years in prison and 325 million in fines 
the six other defendants faced lesser penalties if convicted 
they are william wertz the chief of larouches fund raising edward 
spannaus legal coordinator for larouche and fundraisers paul 
