higher through the middle of next year and will eventually take 
their toll on housing a higher rate increases monthly mortgage 
payments 
rates on fixedrate mortgages which fell from about 10 percent 
in midaugust to 10 percent in late october have since climbed 
back to nearly 10 percent according to the federal home loan 
mortgage corp 
