citizens were selected for interview by the authorities 
despite the problems lurking around the bend czechoslovakia 
currently has the highest standard of living of any communist 
country the governments agreement with the people says the 
narration is well keep your stomachs full if you keep your 
mouths shut 
nevertheless there are tiny signs of change czech filmmakers 
are allowed to tackle such subjects as drug abuse hooliganism 
and the black market in foreign currency and the lack of 
spirituality in the society has sparked a new interest in religion 
especially among young people 
the film a production of wttw in chicago was produced by george 
vicas a veteran television journalist who started out with the 
