<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures on the dominican republic 
the land the dominican republic makes up the eastern twothirds 
of the caribbean island of hispaniola which it shares with haiti 
its area of 18700 square miles is roughly size of vermont and new 
hampshire combined the terraian ranges from fertile plains to 
mountains and deserts pico duarte at 10206 feet is the highest 
mountain in caribbean the climate is subtropical with an average 
temperature of 77 degrees its main agricultural products are sugar 
cocoa coffee tobacco and rice 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history the island was discovered by columbus in 1492 on his 
first voyage to new world and was was ceded by spain to france in 
1697 haiti held the entire island from 1822 until 1844 when the 
independent dominican republic was established the republic was 
annexed to spain from 1861 to 1865 when independence was restored 
unrest brought an invasion by us marines in 1916 and a military 
government was in place until 1924 gen rafael l trujillo took 
power in 1930 and established a repressive dictatorship that ended 
with his assassination in 1961 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people the population of about 66 million is 
spanishspeaking seventyfive percent are of mixed race 15 percent 
white and 10 percent black ninetyeight percent are roman catholic 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
government executive power is vested under the 1966 
constitution in a president elected by popular vote every four 
years its bicameral congress consists of a 27member senate 
representing 26 provinces and district of santo domingo and a 92 
member chamber of deputies the ninemember supreme court is chosen 
by the senate 
