prehistoric caves in france and spain romes 
coliseum or athens acropolis egypts mystic pyramids its hard to 
imagine the mediterranean world without its most famous landmarks 
but the areas monuments face an uncertain future as they become 
caught up in a push toward lucrative mass tourism that could 
endanger them 
indicative of the dilemma facing the regions planners is the 
view of sayed moussa egypts head of tourism promotion who 
