after the hearing himmel and the affablelooking rough declined 
to comment 
the indictment said that while rough was president of the 
national bank of sussex county in branchville nj and sat on the 
new york feds board from 1982 to 1984 he regularly leaked advance 
word on the local federal reserves discount rate recommendation to 
the national fed as well as the feds final determination on the 
rate 
the discount rate has a powerful effect on the securities market 
and has been called by fed officials one of their most closely 
guarded secrets the rate is the interest the fed charges on loans 
to financial institutions and is regarded as an indicator of the 
direction in which the fed is seeking to push interest rates which 
affect the prices of bonds 
after the fed learned of the allegations against rough which 
were first mentioned in april 1987 during testimony at a criminal 
trial stemming from the bevill bresler collapse the bank tightened 
procedures for the rate rough publicly denied the charges at the 
time of the trial repeating denials to investigators in private 
interviews 
rough a former chairman of the new jersey bankers association 
was formally charged with conspiracy to commit wire and securities 
fraud two counts of bank fraud one count each of wire fraud and 
securities fraud and two counts of making false statements to banks 
authorities have called it the first case of insider trading 
involving government securities and the federal reserve system 
rough resigned from sussex national earlier this year 
prosecutors said 
