again decline next spring this also moderates price gains for 
chemicals and plastics 
ratajcak said he expects that for 1988 in total wholesale prices 
will have risen 37 percent compared with 22 percent for last 
year for 1989 he is predicting wholesale price inflation of 42 
percent with beef and pork costs soaring in the second wave of 
aftershocks from last summers drought 
when the opec agreement becomes unmanagable next spring and oil 
prices decline once again commodity inflation should remain 
restrained he said in the increasing concern about inflation 
