platinum futures prices plunged the permitted limit of 25 an 
ounce for the second straight day friday but cash prices steadied as 
players reassessed the likely market impact of ford motor cos 
platinumfree catalytic converter 
on other markets coffee futures roared to a sixmonth high and 
prices of palladium gold silver grain soybean energy cattle 
pork and stockindex futures all rose 
platinum for january delivery on the new york mercantile exchange 
settled at 55450 a troy ounce as traders attempted to bring the 
price of the nearmonth futures contract into line with the spot 
price for platinum 
spot platinum had tumbled from around 600 to about 532 an ounce 
thursday on news that ford planned to test an automobile catalytic 
converter that did not use the rare and costly metal 
the use of platinum as a catalyst in the pollutioncontrol 
devices accounts for more than onethird of world platinum 
consumption 
spot platinum settled 710 lower friday on the new york merc at 
52480 an ounce after trading as low as 517 but analysts citing 
tight supplies and strong nearterm demand for the metal said the 
markets had overreacted to fords announcement 
its going to take some time before the shift to the new 
