<TEXT>
by george garties 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
federal express corp agreed friday to buy the 
parent of the flying tigers air freight line in an 880 million deal 
that would give the overnightpackage company a foothold in the 
international air cargo business 
the purchase of tiger international inc would combine memphis 
tennbased federal express the nations biggest express package 
shipper with the cargo carrier founded by american pilots who 
volunteered to fly for china in the early years of world war ii 
under an agreement approved by the boards of directors of both 
companies federal express will make a 2087 a share cash tender 
offer dec 20 for all tiger internationals 408 million common 
shares and equivalents 
when financing costs and the cost of outstanding warrants and 
employee options to buy tiger international stock are included the 
value of the deal is 880 million said federal express spokesman 
armand schneider 
tiger international stock jumped 250 to 1937 a share on the 
new york stock exchange federal express dipped 50 cents to 4675 
the offer is conditioned on at least 501 percent of the flying 
tigers stock being tendered 
the merger is subject to the approval of the us transportation 
department and antitrust clearance from the justice department 
stockholders of both companies must also vote on the buyout 
federal express which covers the united states with 104 cargo 
jets and 137 smaller planes has had its eye on the international 
market for some time and has established routes to brussels and 
tokyo federal express carries overnight and secondday letters and 
packages of up to 150 pounds 
the company has 63000 employees worldwide 
flying tiger with 37 cargo jets and two passenger airliners has 
scheduled cargo service to north and south america asia europe 
the south pacific and the middle east 
frederick smith chief executive officer for federal express 
said the combination of flying tigers international route 
authorities highly efficient cargo fleet and strategically located 
airport facilities will enable federal express to accelerate the 
development of its global distribution network 
saul steinberg tiger international cochairman and controller of 
148 percent of the company through his reliance group holdings 
inc called the deal a fair one for tiger shareholders 
rumors that steinberg was interested in selling the company to 
maximize his investment have circulated occasionally for more than a 
year and a half 
in tiger international federal express gets a company with a 
colorful history that only recently clawed its way back from the 
brink of liquidation 
flying tiger was founded in 1945 by pilots who fought with maj 
gen claire chennaults fighter group of the same name the flying 
tigers who went to china in 1941 to fly missions against the 
japanese later became part of the us army air force 
the fliers civilian enterprise was the worlds first scheduled 
air cargo line and claims to be the biggest it has about 6500 
employees 
but tiger almost was forced into liquidation in 1986 after a run 
of losses blamed on illfated diversification moves high salaries 
and high fuel prices 
a lastminute agreement by workers to take pay cuts and make 
workrule concessions averted sale of the fleet and the company 
moved back into the black last year paying employees 16 million in 
profitsharing that was part of the recovery deal 
a decision has yet to be made on whether tiger will retain its 
identity the companies said 
federal express has ridden a boom in overnight mail for some 
years but acknowledges that the proliferation of facsimile machines 
which deliver photocopies instantly by telephone has slowed the 
growth of its business 
it has been rumored for some time to be interested in getting 
into the cargo business 
federal express posted a profit of 1188 million on sales of 
22 billion in the first six months of the current fiscal year 
federal express flies 80 boeing 727s 24 mcdonnell douglas dc10s 
and 137 smaller cessna and fokker turboprop planes 
tiger earned 328 million on sales of 6398 million in the 
first six months 
tiger flies 20 boeing 747s six dc8s and 11 boeing 727s it 
also has two boeing 747 passenger planes used for military contract 
flights 6500 
</TEXT>
