<TEXT>
inflation at the wholesale level maintained its moderate pace 
during november while housing construction soared to its highest 
point in seven months the government said 
the labor department reported friday that wholesale prices rose 
03 percent in november as food costs showed no increases for the 
second straight month the stable food prices helped offset large 
increases for gasoline and heating oil 
the report helped to weaken theories that inflation is worsening 
the november increase if it persisted for 12 months would amount 
to an annual inflation rate of just 33 percent lower than the 38 
percent annualized rate for the first 11 months of 1987 
inflationary fears exceed inflationary reality at the present 
time said donald ratajczak director of economic forecasting at 
georgia state university in atlanta 
in another report friday the commerce department said new homes 
and apartments were built at a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 
156 million units last month up from the 154 million rate in 
october 
it was the third increase in a row and the highest level of 
construction activity since april housing starts soared 51 percent 
in october and rose 04 percent in september 
housing permits a good barometer of future housing activity 
edged up 01 percent to a ratould have cost 10970 last month 40 
cents more than in october 
